<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: Keeping your eyes on the size]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=16017&amp;p=197281#p197281"><![CDATA[
256b demos usually have custom code generators build in them, you can't really get generic code packer for that size <img src="http://forums.nesdev.com/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif" alt=";)" title="Wink" /> And making something fractal also helps <img src="http://forums.nesdev.com/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif" alt=";)" title="Wink" /><br /><br />4K demos, it starts to get to the point where your encode you opcode stream and param streams separately, as you will typically do a <br />LDA XXXX<br />STA XXXX<br />LDA XXXX<br />STA XXXX<br />type code where the XXXXs will be different, but this way you can compress the LDA STA run, and then the hi bytes normally have a run so you get the unique lows and RLE the common His etc.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=8250">Oziphantom</a> — Sat Jun 03, 2017 8:02 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
