If a large range of addresses needs to be set either to #$00 or #$FF, you could encode the addresses in a bitpattern.<br /><br />%1001 could mean a 1 (/2/4 however) byte run of #$FF, #$00, #$00, #$FF each written to $21xx.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=355">ccovell</a> — Sat Jun 03, 2017 2:23 am</p><hr />
